<DocsLayout title="Getting Started" description="Quick start guide for LeadEcho — Docker setup, manual development, first steps.">
  <h1>Getting Started</h1>

  <p style="margin-top: 16px;">
    Get LeadEcho running locally in under five minutes using Docker Compose,
    or set up a full development environment for contributing.
  </p>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Requirement</th>
        <th>Version</th>
        <th>Notes</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Docker</td>
        <td>24+</td>
        <td>Required for the recommended quick start</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Docker Compose</td>
        <td>v2.x</td>
        <td>Included with Docker Desktop</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Go</td>
        <td>1.25+</td>
        <td>Optional — only needed for local backend dev</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Node.js + pnpm</td>
        <td>Node 20+, pnpm 9+</td>
        <td>Optional — only needed for dashboard/extension dev</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Quick Start (Docker)</h2>

  <p>The fastest path to a running instance:</p>

  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/rohansx/leadecho
cd leadecho
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env — set JWT_SECRET and at least one AI key
docker compose up -d
make migrate-up</code></pre>

  <h3>Default Ports</h3>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Service</th>
        <th>URL</th>
        <th>Notes</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Dashboard</td>
        <td><code>http://localhost:3100</code></td>
        <td>React SPA</td>
      </tr>
