      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>With Browser Sidecars</h2>

  <p>
    Browser sidecars enable authenticated crawling of Reddit, Twitter, and LinkedIn.
    They run as separate Docker containers alongside the main stack.
  </p>

  <h3>Pinchtab (Reddit, Twitter, LinkedIn)</h3>

  <pre><code># Start with Pinchtab sidecar
docker compose --profile browser up -d

# Required env vars:
# PINCHTAB_TOKEN=your-token
# PINCHTAB_URL=http://localhost:9867  (default)</code></pre>

  <h3>Camoufox Pro (stealth LinkedIn)</h3>

  <pre><code># Start with Camoufox sidecar (Pro tier)
CAMOUFOX_URL=http://localhost:9868 docker compose --profile browser-pro up -d</code></pre>

  <h3>Scrapling (fallback)</h3>

  <pre><code># Adaptive CSS-based extraction fallback
docker compose --profile browser-scrapling up -d</code></pre>

  <h2>Manual Development Setup</h2>

  <p>For local development with hot-reload:</p>

  <pre><code># Install all dependencies
make install

# Start all services (backend + dashboard + postgres + redis)
make up

# Tail all logs
make logs

# Regenerate Go types after SQL changes
make sqlc

# TypeScript type check
make web-check</code></pre>

  <h3>Backend Only</h3>

  <pre><code>cd backend
go run ./cmd/api/main.go</code></pre>

  <h3>Dashboard Only</h3>

  <pre><code>cd dashboard
pnpm dev</code></pre>

  <h3>Extension Development</h3>

  <pre><code>cd extension
pnpm install
pnpm dev   # watches and rebuilds on change</code></pre>

  <h2>First Steps After Install</h2>

  <ol>
    <li>Open <a href="http://localhost:3100">http://localhost:3100</a> and register an account.</li>
    <li>Complete the onboarding wizard — it guides you through keyword setup and AI key configuration.</li>
    <li>Add your first keyword under <strong>Keywords</strong> in the sidebar.</li>
    <li>Configure AI keys in <strong>Settings → API Keys</strong> (GLM or OpenAI required).</li>
    <li>Optionally add a Voyage AI key for semantic pain-point matching.</li>
    <li>Wait for the first scan cycle — the monitor runs every 5 minutes by default.</li>
    <li>Incoming matches appear in <strong>Inbox</strong> with AI-assigned relevance scores.</li>
  </ol>

  <blockquote>
    <p>
      <strong>Tip:</strong> Without a Voyage AI key, LeadEcho falls back to keyword-only matching.
      Semantic matching is significantly more accurate — grab a free key at
      <a href="https://www.voyageai.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">voyageai.com</a>.
    </p>
  </blockquote>

  <h2>Makefile Commands Reference</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Command</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>make install</code></td>
        <td>Install all Go and Node dependencies</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>make up</code></td>
        <td>Start all services via Docker Compose</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>make down</code></td>
        <td>Stop all services</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>make logs</code></td>
        <td>Tail all service logs</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>make migrate-up</code></td>
        <td>Run pending database migrations</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>make migrate-down</code></td>
        <td>Roll back last migration</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>make sqlc</code></td>
        <td>Regenerate Go types from SQL queries</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>make web-check</code></td>
        <td>TypeScript type check for dashboard</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>make build</code></td>
        <td>Build all Docker images</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</DocsLayout>
